	   <tr><td colspan=2>The wine quest is a section of Book of Turmoil quest.  If you give a bottle of red wine to Lokar To' Biath your faction goes up with the Dark Bargainers and the Dread Inner Guard and Dread Outer Guard.  You could run through the quest up to the point where you get the book, but you're playing with fire as it requires you to run back and forth between the library in 3rd Gate and the Blind Fish in Commons near the bank.  But you get several faction hits with each part you complete and no negative adjustments until you kill Lokar then it goes down with the Dark Bargainers.  However, when you turn in his head, you get another faction boost as well as the Book of Turmoil.  Its a nifty quest I ran my DE wizard through when he was 12th level and he cons warmly to the merchants in Neriak now.<br>Another possibility is to turn in lightstones and greater lightstones to Smith Tv' ysa at the dark elf camp in South Ro. (co-ords approx. 100 499) You get a concordance of research for each greater lightstone and one of two research books for casters for regular lightstones and faction boosts for the Dark Bargainers and Dread Inner Guard and Dread Outer Guard.  My wood elf ranger conned dubiously to her at the onset but she accepted the lightstone and I got the faction adjustment on experimentation.  This is also a quest that gives nice experience for each lightstone submitted until about level 14 then its just faction adjustments.   <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
